  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You immediately create two bone weapons (one per hand). While in this stance, you can retract and extend these weapons into (and from) your body as a move action. The weapons are part of your body, and any damage dealt to them is therefor dealt to you. In addi- tion, when you are struck in melee with an unarmed attack, or with a held weapon of Small or smaller size, you can spend 4 Chakra to sprout sharp bones in retaliation, dealing 1d6+1 piercing damage to the attacker. You can do this only once per round.<br><br>When the technique ends, the bone weapons return to your body.</p>\n\n\n\n",
